l=1
p(yl|y<l, x‚â§l), (1)
where yl is the l-th language token of the input text, y<l is the set of preceding tokens, x‚â§l is the set of images/videos preceding token yl in the interleaved sequence and p is parametrized by a Flamingo model. The ability to handle interleaved text and visual sequences (Section 2.3) makes it natural to use Flamingo models for in-context few-shot learning, analogously to GPT-3 with few-shot text prompting. The model is trained on a diverse mixture of datasets as described in Section 2.4.
